WEBVTT

00:11.344 --> 00:13.212
         - So how was your night
                     last night?

00:13.214 --> 00:14.747
            Do anything special?

00:14.749 --> 00:17.016
- [laughs]

00:18.752 --> 00:20.753
Yeah, it was amazing.

00:20.755 --> 00:23.422
           - It was?
           - [laughs]

00:26.092 --> 00:29.595
So, I mean,
what do we do now?

00:29.597 --> 00:33.465
          - How about we keep it
                      undefined?

00:33.467 --> 00:36.735
            For now.
            - Okay.

00:44.778 --> 00:48.180
Hey, as long as
you come over tonight, okay?

00:48.182 --> 00:52.484
        - Uh, what time?
           - [laughs]

00:52.486 --> 00:57.056
         <i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:57.058 --> 00:58.323
Sean!

00:58.325 --> 01:01.060
           [gunshots]

01:01.062 --> 01:02.594
[gasping]
Sean!

01:02.596 --> 01:04.530
           - Go! Go!
          Go get him!

01:04.532 --> 01:07.332
- Stop!
Police!

01:07.334 --> 01:10.402
           [panting]

01:11.771 --> 01:13.338
           [gunshot]

01:14.274 --> 01:20.279
               <i>â™ª </i>

01:20.281 --> 01:22.514
            Police!
          Don't move!

01:24.451 --> 01:25.684
            Police!

01:25.686 --> 01:28.454
          - [screams]

01:28.456 --> 01:30.355
          - Stay down!
         - You shot me.

01:30.357 --> 01:31.623
       - Don't you move!
         - You shot me!

01:31.625 --> 01:33.859
       - Don't you move!
  - You shot me! You shot me!

01:33.861 --> 01:36.361
          - Stay down!
         - You shot me!

01:36.363 --> 01:38.764
      Why you shot me for?
      - Yeah, I shot you!

01:38.766 --> 01:40.833
    - I didn't do anything!
     - You shot my partner!

01:40.835 --> 01:42.434
    - I didn't do anything!
         - You mother--

01:42.436 --> 01:44.603
   what the hell did you do?
           - [crying]

01:44.605 --> 01:46.305
  - What the hell did you do?
         - You shot me!

01:46.307 --> 01:47.573
- What is your problem?
Stay down!

01:47.575 --> 01:48.774
     - What are you doing?

01:48.776 --> 01:50.476
                         [yells]
           I didn't do anything!

01:50.478 --> 01:52.344
            - Sean!

01:52.346 --> 01:53.779
           I repeat,
   officer and offender down!

01:53.781 --> 01:55.881
      Roll two ambulances
      to 580 West Cermak!

01:55.883 --> 01:57.883
         My partner's been shot.
           Offender's been shot.

01:57.885 --> 02:01.120
      Sean, are you okay?
             Sean!

02:01.122 --> 02:02.488
          Are you hit
         anywhere else?

02:02.490 --> 02:04.323
    Sean, please talk to me!

02:04.325 --> 02:05.691
         Just show me!

02:05.693 --> 02:07.826
       Please don't die!
       Please don't die!

02:07.828 --> 02:09.261
             Sean!

02:11.000 --> 02:17.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:18.905 --> 02:20.806
       - How many shots?
      - Four? Maybe five.

02:20.808 --> 02:22.674
and then Roman,
he screams at me to go.

02:22.676 --> 02:24.143
        - He said that?
             - Yes.

02:24.145 --> 02:25.878
So I chased that little prick
to that corner,

02:25.880 --> 02:27.279
he fires at me
two more times.

02:27.281 --> 02:28.680
I tell him to stop

02:28.682 --> 02:31.250
and then he turns,
looks over his shoulder,

02:31.252 --> 02:33.218
something silver
in his hand, so I fired.

02:33.220 --> 02:34.620
         - You kept sight on him
                 the whole time?

02:34.622 --> 02:36.622
- No, not when he
rounded the corner.

02:38.424 --> 02:40.626
But I only had my eye off him
for a few seconds,

02:40.628 --> 02:42.227
it's the same kid.

02:42.229 --> 02:43.929
         - You get a look at him
       as he approached the car?

02:43.931 --> 02:46.832
- Maybe a glimpse.
Mostly just arm and torso,

02:46.834 --> 02:48.367
gun and muzzle flashes.

02:48.369 --> 02:50.402
Silver gun,
it looked like a .9.

02:50.404 --> 02:52.337
- Did you see where the asswipe
       tossed the piece?

02:52.339 --> 02:54.940
            - What?
        - Can't find it.

02:59.946 --> 03:02.781
        - You all right?
      - Yes. How is Sean?

03:02.783 --> 03:04.516
   - He lost a lot of blood.

03:04.518 --> 03:07.452
       - Marine Unit is en route
                to find the gun.

03:07.454 --> 03:09.221
      - You hit him twice
       from 40 yards away

03:09.223 --> 03:11.423
         in low light?
           Nice job.

03:15.728 --> 03:18.730
                          - Kim.
                 Kim, come here.

03:18.732 --> 03:20.566
                  You got to put
           a statement together.

03:20.568 --> 03:21.900
           Okay? List everything
                  that happened.

03:21.902 --> 03:23.902
                  Be definitive.

03:23.904 --> 03:25.804
              Keep your feelings
                      out of it.

03:25.806 --> 03:28.974
              Everything you say
        will be carved in stone.

03:28.976 --> 03:31.777
- I want to get to Med.

03:31.779 --> 03:33.845
                      - After.

03:38.384 --> 03:40.519
      - 17-year-old male.
         Multiple GSWs.

03:40.521 --> 03:41.987
    One in the lower flank,
     one in the left thigh.

03:41.989 --> 03:45.257
                 No exit wounds.
              GCS 15, BP 166/72.

03:45.259 --> 03:46.391
        Heart rate 128.
          - All right.

03:46.393 --> 03:47.793
Dr. Choi,
you're going to Baghdad.

03:47.795 --> 03:49.461
           - Got it!
    - Talk to me, incoming!

03:49.463 --> 03:50.929
   - 27-year-old police officer.

03:50.931 --> 03:54.233
Gunshot wound to the right neck,
       left back, arm, and hand.

03:54.235 --> 03:57.603
              GCS 15, BPs 94/60.
                Heart rates 122.

03:57.605 --> 03:59.404
      - All right, rotate.
    We're going to Trauma 2.

03:59.406 --> 04:00.973
  - No, no, he goes with Choi!
   - Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey!

04:00.975 --> 04:04.643
      - He goes with Choi!
     [overlapping shouting]

04:04.645 --> 04:06.912
      - Everyone shut up!
       - Maggie, come on!

04:06.914 --> 04:09.348
- Go into Trauma 2!

04:09.350 --> 04:11.583
- Everybody block out the noise.
              Let's get to work.

04:11.585 --> 04:14.753
   - And every police officer
clear into the waiting room now!

04:14.755 --> 04:18.357
             Move!
          Move! Move!

04:18.358 --> 04:20.993
       Get out of my ER!

04:20.995 --> 04:24.463
- Michael Vance Ellis.
17. No priors.

04:24.465 --> 04:25.764
Father, John Ellis,
is a plumber,

04:25.766 --> 04:27.666
mother, Cecily Ellis,
works at a bank.

04:27.668 --> 04:30.402
We're running their address for
any historical in-service calls.

04:30.404 --> 04:32.638
               - Roman and Ellis
     are both in surgery at Med.

04:32.640 --> 04:34.606
       Ellis' parents are there.

04:34.608 --> 04:36.408
- You got surveillance footage?
            - Yeah.

04:36.410 --> 04:39.344
I'm uploading the POD
footage right here.

04:48.388 --> 04:51.390
          <i>[somber music]</i>

04:51.392 --> 04:54.660
         - It's unreal.
   - Just like Philadelphia.

04:54.662 --> 04:56.895
          - That your statement?

04:56.897 --> 04:58.797
            - Yeah.
           - Come on.

04:58.799 --> 05:00.832
      All right, you're gonna go
                 into my office,

05:00.834 --> 05:02.434
       I'm gonna close the door,

05:02.436 --> 05:04.636
                  and I need you
               to memorize this.

05:04.638 --> 05:06.738
Every word.

05:10.910 --> 05:12.544
              - Marine Unit says
                     no gun yet.

05:12.546 --> 05:14.813
           - [sighs]
            - Great.

05:14.815 --> 05:17.849
- Assistant State's
Attorney is downstairs.

05:17.851 --> 05:19.384
                 - Who'd we get?

05:19.386 --> 05:20.986
- Peter Stone.

05:29.095 --> 05:31.063
     - What was that about?

05:31.065 --> 05:33.999
               - Stone's the guy
         who sent him to prison.

05:41.007 --> 05:43.909
            - Peter.

05:43.911 --> 05:46.011
            - Hank.

05:47.980 --> 05:50.515
    Officer Roman's in ICU?
        - That's right.

05:50.517 --> 05:52.918
- And Officer Burgess?
How's she holding up?

05:52.920 --> 05:55.020
   - As well as can be expected.

05:56.356 --> 05:58.457
- What kind of a cop is she?

05:59.992 --> 06:02.794
                       - A plus.

06:02.796 --> 06:04.363
- I'm gonna need
the General Progress Reports

06:04.365 --> 06:06.365
from the incident--
plus any CRs on both

06:06.367 --> 06:07.866
Officers Roman and Burgess.

06:07.868 --> 06:10.001
  - They're active cops, they're
   gonna have complaint reports.

06:10.003 --> 06:13.972
We have 42 hours to either
charge or release Mr. Ellis.

06:13.974 --> 06:16.074
              - Yeah, I'm aware.

06:17.076 --> 06:18.810
               Feed you the info
                    as I get it.

06:18.812 --> 06:20.612
- I appreciate that,
but because of the profile

06:20.614 --> 06:22.013
of the incident,
we'll be doing

06:22.015 --> 06:24.683
a parallel and
independent investigation.

06:24.685 --> 06:27.819
My people are already
talking to the victim.

06:27.821 --> 06:30.422
        - This is a clean shoot,
                          Peter.

06:30.424 --> 06:31.823
- I sure hope so.

06:31.825 --> 06:33.925
You get me
those reports ASAP.

06:46.707 --> 06:49.841
I'm Detective Halstead,
this is Detective Lindsay.

06:49.843 --> 06:51.977
        - They're saying
    Michael shot the police.

06:51.979 --> 06:53.445
- Yeah, he did.

06:53.447 --> 06:55.080
         - That couldn't happen.
               It just couldn't.

06:55.082 --> 06:56.948
        - That's what we're here
                  to figure out.

06:56.950 --> 06:58.750
                   Does your son
           have access to a gun?

06:58.752 --> 07:01.119
- No! No knife,
no gun, no nothing.

07:01.121 --> 07:02.854
Not in my house.

07:02.856 --> 07:04.489
- You have to believe us.

07:04.491 --> 07:07.192
Michael doesn't have
a mean bone in his body.

07:07.194 --> 07:10.996
He's a Chicago Scholar.
He's on the Honor Roll.

07:10.998 --> 07:14.433
        - There's no way
     he could've done this.

07:14.435 --> 07:18.170
- My son didn't do this!
[crying]

07:19.772 --> 07:22.607
          [whispering]
       He didn't do this.

07:35.621 --> 07:37.722
                       - [gasps]

07:38.658 --> 07:40.759
- It's okay.

07:46.833 --> 07:48.200
          - I'm sorry.

07:49.735 --> 07:52.204
        - I'm all over the news.

07:52.206 --> 07:54.639
- Yeah, I know.

07:59.679 --> 08:01.813
Kim...

08:04.517 --> 08:07.619
I know you and I ended
pretty rough,

08:07.621 --> 08:11.590
but, hey...

08:11.592 --> 08:13.959
I still care about you
a lot

08:13.961 --> 08:15.560
and...

08:15.562 --> 08:18.163
if you need anything
at all...

08:19.565 --> 08:22.234
I'm here.
I got your back.

08:27.940 --> 08:29.641
Okay?

08:37.549 --> 08:39.650
        - Tell us what happened,
                        Michael.

08:40.986 --> 08:43.554
- This guy ran around a corner.

08:43.557 --> 08:45.524
 Fired a gun a couple of times
        then ducked off

08:45.526 --> 08:48.793
        into a building
     like 20 feet from me.

08:48.795 --> 08:51.096
        I started to run
  'cause this kid was shooting

08:51.098 --> 08:54.766
       and I didn't know
       what was going on.

08:54.768 --> 08:56.935
Next thing I know,

08:56.937 --> 08:58.003
I hear this
woman's voice yelling

08:58.005 --> 09:01.106
so I turned and ran.

09:01.108 --> 09:04.543
       Then it felt like
I got punched hard in the back.

09:07.580 --> 09:09.681
     That's all I remember.

09:14.587 --> 09:17.022
      Now they telling me
   I might never walk again.

09:17.024 --> 09:18.156
- [whispers]
Oh, God.

09:18.158 --> 09:21.259
[crying]
My baby.

09:25.298 --> 09:28.867
                      - Michael,
             did you have a gun?

09:28.869 --> 09:30.201
             - No.

09:30.203 --> 09:32.203
- What were you doing
down by the water?

09:32.205 --> 09:35.240
  This girl I've been seeing,
     she broke up with me.

09:35.242 --> 09:38.043
   I just wanted to be alone.

09:41.347 --> 09:43.348
        That lady cop...

09:43.350 --> 09:45.650
      shot the wrong guy.

09:54.894 --> 09:57.629
          - We finished the IPR,
    separated by family members,

09:57.631 --> 09:59.831
               known associates,
         neighbors, and schools.

09:59.833 --> 10:02.200
  We did not find one witness
         who would say

10:02.202 --> 10:03.868
     this kid was anything
      but an Eagle Scout.

10:03.870 --> 10:05.370
       - Gang Investigation says
             they don't have him

10:05.372 --> 10:06.705
         affiliated with anyone.

10:06.707 --> 10:08.206
               Not one gang card
            or disbursal on him.

10:08.208 --> 10:10.809
     - Gunshot residue test
on Ellis came back inconclusive,

10:10.811 --> 10:12.944
      because of the water
         he fell into.

10:12.946 --> 10:16.047
         [phone rings]

10:16.949 --> 10:20.185
Patel.
Yes, sir.

10:21.787 --> 10:23.888
             Okay.

10:23.890 --> 10:25.991
Boss needs an update.

10:32.865 --> 10:34.332
He's on his way.

10:34.334 --> 10:36.334
          - No weapon.

10:36.336 --> 10:38.703
  No continuous line of sight.

10:38.705 --> 10:41.673
    No independent witnesses
       to any part of it.

10:43.009 --> 10:45.944
        What do we have?
       - Officer Burgess.

10:47.046 --> 10:49.347
- We actually have more evidence
against her than Ellis.

10:49.349 --> 10:51.049
   - She made a positive ID.

10:51.051 --> 10:54.819
  - The single most unreliable
   type of ID: eyewitnesses.

10:54.821 --> 10:57.889
   - Oh, come on, we all know
   what happened that night.

10:57.891 --> 11:00.091
         The other guy
    Ellis said was shooting?

11:00.093 --> 11:01.726
    He's not on any cameras.

11:01.728 --> 11:04.062
        And the building
    he supposedly ran into?

11:04.064 --> 11:06.331
    One door, triple locked
        from the inside.

11:06.333 --> 11:08.433
     Houdini couldn't have
           gotten in.

11:10.002 --> 11:12.837
           - No gun.
       Shot in the back.

11:14.140 --> 11:17.208
   You rush to edict this kid
     and we get it wrong...

11:18.678 --> 11:20.779
   This city's gonna explode.

11:28.954 --> 11:31.056
- You know what
I can't figure out?

11:33.893 --> 11:36.094
      Is <i>why</i> Ellis did it.

11:36.096 --> 11:38.196
       It doesn't add up.

11:39.398 --> 11:41.399
      How do you graduate
     from having no priors

11:41.401 --> 11:43.368
       to trying to kill
           two cops?

11:43.370 --> 11:45.470
            - We may never know.

11:46.739 --> 11:48.473
       - I need to know.

11:48.475 --> 11:52.143
 in the case to bring charges.
- Don't tell me. Don't tell me.

11:52.145 --> 11:53.878
- Michael Ellis
is free to go home

11:53.880 --> 11:55.280
 once he's discharged from Med.
   - You're making a mistake.

11:55.282 --> 11:59.084
   - Don't blow smoke up my ass.
                      You caved.

11:59.086 --> 12:02.053
   This case is gonna get shoved
    in a file cabinet somewhere.

12:02.055 --> 12:03.722
- That's where you're wrong.

12:03.724 --> 12:05.256
Someone's getting charged.

12:05.258 --> 12:07.358
I just don't know who yet.

12:11.230 --> 12:12.964
           - [sighs]

12:15.935 --> 12:18.303
           - [sighs]
   - You called me in, Sarge?

12:23.142 --> 12:25.744
- [exhales, clears throat]

12:25.746 --> 12:27.445
"Officer Burgess,
you have been

12:27.447 --> 12:29.948
"officially relieved
of your police powers and duties

12:29.950 --> 12:32.016
             "pending separation
           from this department.

12:32.018 --> 12:35.086
             "You no longer have
the authority to carry a weapon.

12:35.088 --> 12:37.088
                 "If you on-view
               any criminal acts

12:37.090 --> 12:40.291
              "you must call 911
      and take no police action.

12:40.293 --> 12:42.894
                "Did you clearly
    and intelligently understand

12:42.896 --> 12:44.963
each and every
one of these orders?"

12:49.368 --> 12:51.469
                          - Yes.

13:00.913 --> 13:02.781
     [protesters chanting]
     Hands up, don't shoot!

13:02.783 --> 13:04.149
     Hands up, don't shoot!

13:04.151 --> 13:07.185
     Hands up, don't shoot!
     Hands up, don't shoot!

13:07.187 --> 13:10.088
     Hands up, don't shoot!
     Hands up, don't shoot!

13:10.090 --> 13:12.991
  - Another unarmed black man
        shot in Chicago!

13:12.993 --> 13:14.793
     Shot in the back too.
      [chanting continues]

13:14.795 --> 13:16.227
Tell me something, brother,

13:16.229 --> 13:18.797
you like shooting
at your own people?

13:18.799 --> 13:20.865
                       - Really?

13:20.867 --> 13:22.400
      Watch yourself, man.
      - What you 'gon do?

13:22.402 --> 13:25.103
      [chanting continues]
     Hands up, don't shoot!

13:25.105 --> 13:28.006
     Hands up, don't shoot!
     Hands up, don't shoot!

13:28.008 --> 13:31.009
         <i>[dramatic music]</i>

13:31.011 --> 13:34.412
               <i>â™ª </i>

13:34.414 --> 13:37.415
                          - Hey.
   Got here as fast as we could.

13:37.417 --> 13:39.417
  - Called in some more hands.

13:39.419 --> 13:42.554
- The incident took place
at 580 West Cermak street?

13:42.556 --> 13:44.022
                      - Correct.

13:44.024 --> 13:46.324
- Isn't that...

13:46.326 --> 13:48.426
three blocks off
your assigned beat?

13:51.931 --> 13:53.932
     - We went on the zone,
         told dispatch

13:53.934 --> 13:55.333
       we were going down
         on a personal.

13:55.335 --> 13:57.135
              - Officer Burgess,
      did you notice anyone else

13:57.137 --> 13:59.270
         walking around the area
            before the shooting?

13:59.272 --> 14:01.406
             - No.
     It's all in my report.

14:06.278 --> 14:09.914
   - So how long had you been
 going out with Michael Ellis?

14:09.916 --> 14:11.449
- Few months.

14:11.451 --> 14:15.353
                - But you're not
               together anymore?

14:15.355 --> 14:18.056
          - No, ma'am.

14:18.058 --> 14:19.924
      - Why'd you guys break up?

14:19.926 --> 14:22.126
          - I told him we needed
                to slow it down.

14:22.128 --> 14:24.095
           I didn't mean for him
            to take it that way.

14:24.097 --> 14:28.032
          - What way?
      - Like we were over.

14:28.034 --> 14:30.134
I told him that.

14:32.972 --> 14:34.639
         - You and Michael Ellis
         worked together, right?

14:34.641 --> 14:36.207
            - Yeah.
   - What kind of kid is he?

14:36.209 --> 14:37.542
        - I don't know.

14:37.544 --> 14:40.278
     - We're not here about
  a stolen purse, Mr. Kelton,

14:40.280 --> 14:41.646
                a police officer
                       was shot.

14:41.648 --> 14:44.015
        If you have information,
            you need to tell us.

14:44.017 --> 14:46.451
- Wish I could help.

14:46.453 --> 14:48.453
- Have you ever been
in jail, Mr. Kelton?

14:48.455 --> 14:50.054
                        - Juvie.
                  Nothing since.

14:50.056 --> 14:52.156
     - You want to go back?
          - For what?

14:52.158 --> 14:54.259
- It's called
hindering a prosecution.

14:54.261 --> 14:56.361
Three to five.

14:58.931 --> 15:00.999
                         - Okay.

15:01.001 --> 15:04.535
                      On Friday,
          Mike was all agitated.

15:04.537 --> 15:08.373
And then he just started
ranting about--

15:08.375 --> 15:10.909
             about Chicago cops.

15:10.911 --> 15:13.278
      - What about Chicago cops?

15:13.280 --> 15:15.346
                - Said they were
                 out of control.

15:15.348 --> 15:18.583
            That no one ever did
                    anything it.

15:23.222 --> 15:25.189
    - Well, I got something.

15:25.191 --> 15:26.591
                  Michael Ellis,
          his Instagram account,

15:26.593 --> 15:28.192
                   he deleted it
      a day before the shooting.

15:28.194 --> 15:29.460
- Right.

15:29.462 --> 15:31.529
             - I pulled this off
       the girlfriend's account.

15:37.269 --> 15:40.004
    - Honor student my ass.

15:40.006 --> 15:41.272
         <i>[crowd chanting]</i>
      <i>Hands up, don't shoot!</i>

15:41.274 --> 15:43.107
     <i>Hands up, don't shoot! </i>
        <i>- Get out front</i>

15:43.109 --> 15:45.109
      and set a parameter
     with the blue horses,

15:45.111 --> 15:47.345
                  and, remember,
     everyone has a camera phone

15:47.347 --> 15:50.315
