          - I actually came here
                 to talk to you.

33:37.548 --> 33:38.749
- Back here.

33:38.751 --> 33:41.018
- Dewan Motley
from six years ago.

33:41.020 --> 33:42.486
You were the desk sergeant
on duty that night.

33:42.488 --> 33:44.254
            - I was?
    - The arresting officer,

33:44.256 --> 33:47.090
                     Ed Braymer,
    what kind of officer was he?

33:47.092 --> 33:50.160
- Old-school.
Very old-school.

33:51.729 --> 33:53.764
Not my kind of cop,
to be honest.

33:56.434 --> 33:58.435
                       - Racist?

33:58.437 --> 34:00.570
                 Off the record.

34:02.040 --> 34:04.141
- Yeah, he was.

34:05.443 --> 34:07.511
Does this have to do
with Michael Ellis?

34:07.513 --> 34:08.645
                        - Maybe.

34:08.647 --> 34:11.081
- It doesn't change
the facts of the case.

34:11.083 --> 34:13.750
     - I'm not talking to you as
  a prosecutor right now, Trudy.

34:13.752 --> 34:16.186
    Nothing excuses what Michael
                 did that night.

34:18.322 --> 34:19.489
       But I think you helped me
                      figure out

34:19.491 --> 34:20.791
               what put that gun
                    in his hand.

34:20.793 --> 34:23.760
         <i>[dramatic music]</i>

34:23.762 --> 34:27.063
               <i>â™ª </i>

34:27.065 --> 34:37.139
 - Defense calls Michael Ellis
         to the stand.

34:51.722 --> 34:55.092
           Michael...
       do you own a gun?

34:55.094 --> 34:56.626
          - No, ma'am.

34:56.628 --> 34:58.228
- Then why did you post
a picture of yourself

34:58.230 --> 35:00.097
holding a gun?

35:00.099 --> 35:01.698
        - It was stupid.

35:01.700 --> 35:03.800
       - Please tell us.

35:07.171 --> 35:08.538
- I was dating Penny

35:08.540 --> 35:11.741
and I got it stuck in my head

35:11.743 --> 35:13.610
    that she wanted someone,
          you know...

35:13.612 --> 35:16.246
            tougher.

35:16.248 --> 35:19.449
 In fact, I'd seen her talking
to some guys who were in gangs.

35:19.451 --> 35:22.252
      I was at this party
 and this older guy had a gun.

35:22.254 --> 35:24.521
     He was showing it off.
      So I was like, "Yo,

35:24.523 --> 35:26.356
    "let me take a photo to,
           you know,

35:26.358 --> 35:30.327
   try to impress this girl."

35:30.329 --> 35:33.630
    That gun was in my hands
    for, like, ten seconds.

35:33.632 --> 35:35.499
          That was it.

35:35.501 --> 35:37.634
        I gave it back.

35:37.636 --> 35:39.736
  I've never even shot a gun.

35:41.772 --> 35:43.840
         - No further questions.

35:50.681 --> 35:53.416
- Who's Dewan Motley?

36:06.230 --> 36:07.764
          - My uncle.

36:07.766 --> 36:10.300
          Well, he's--
   he's not really my uncle.

36:10.302 --> 36:12.536
    - The longtime boyfriend
     of your aunt, correct?

36:13.571 --> 36:15.372
             - Yes.

36:15.374 --> 36:17.607
            - Tell us about him.

36:17.609 --> 36:19.609
- He was a good man.

36:19.611 --> 36:21.611
                    - Is it true
   he was arrested six years ago

36:21.613 --> 36:23.380
     for drunk and disorderly...

36:23.382 --> 36:24.681
             and while resisting
                    that arrest,

36:24.683 --> 36:26.816
 he caught the arresting officer
                    off balance,

36:26.818 --> 36:29.653
         hit him, and caused him
                to hit his head?

36:29.655 --> 36:31.188
                Put that officer
                      in a coma?

36:31.190 --> 36:32.322
    - Objection, Your Honor.
  - And it doesn't look like--

36:32.324 --> 36:33.857
          - Overruled.
     - It doesn't look like

36:33.859 --> 36:36.259
        he's gonna wake up ever.

36:38.596 --> 36:39.729
        Is that correct?

36:39.731 --> 36:42.499
         - Dewan wasn't
     doing anything wrong.

36:42.501 --> 36:43.934
               - Do you remember
  where the incident took place?

36:43.936 --> 36:46.436
  Where your uncle was arrested?

36:46.438 --> 36:47.871
             - No.
   - It was the same street--

36:47.873 --> 36:49.639
                  same corner...

36:49.641 --> 36:51.474
             where Officer Roman
                       was shot.

36:53.377 --> 36:54.644
            - Okay.

36:54.646 --> 36:55.712
      - Did you visit your uncle
                        in jail?

36:55.714 --> 36:56.846
             - Yes.
       - How many times?

36:56.848 --> 36:58.315
        - I don't know.
             - 12.

36:58.317 --> 36:59.816
     - Sidebar, Your Honor.

37:02.286 --> 37:03.687
State never disclosed this.

37:03.689 --> 37:05.355
This is a classic
Brady violation.

37:05.357 --> 37:06.957
- It's newly discovered evidence
             and not exculpatory

37:06.959 --> 37:08.858
so it's not Brady
and how can I disclose something

37:08.860 --> 37:09.993
when I don't even know
they're going to call

37:09.995 --> 37:13.897
- All evidence incriminating
defendant is prejudicial.

37:13.899 --> 37:15.599
Since when is motive
not relevant?

37:15.601 --> 37:18.301
   - This is a collateral issue.
                     No bearing.

37:19.670 --> 37:21.638
  - This is cross examination

37:21.640 --> 37:24.541
      and not exculpatory,
           Counselor.

37:24.543 --> 37:27.244
         I'll allow it.
      Objection overruled.

37:27.246 --> 37:30.680
  - How did Dewan Motley die,
            Michael?

37:30.682 --> 37:32.515
       - He hung himself
           in prison.

37:32.517 --> 37:34.251
         - After his last appeal
                     was denied.

37:34.253 --> 37:35.485
           - I guess.

37:35.487 --> 37:37.687
   - How did that make you feel?

37:37.689 --> 37:39.689
      - How do you think?

37:39.691 --> 37:42.325
               - I'm asking you.

37:44.829 --> 37:46.830
         - I was angry.

37:46.832 --> 37:48.298
       You would be too.

37:48.300 --> 37:50.567
       - When did he die?
    - I don't know for sure.

37:50.569 --> 37:52.002
                - I'll tell you.

37:52.004 --> 37:54.004
          It was the day <i>before </i>

37:54.006 --> 37:55.739
         Officer Roman was shot.

37:57.375 --> 37:59.976
            Michael, look at me.

37:59.978 --> 38:02.279
                      Michael...

38:03.914 --> 38:05.448
                 your girlfriend
               broke up with you

38:05.450 --> 38:08.418
             because you weren't
                  "tough enough"

38:08.420 --> 38:11.755
                and your uncle--
 who's life was ruined by a cop,

38:11.757 --> 38:14.291
                 killed himself.

38:14.293 --> 38:16.660
       This all within two days,
                        correct?

38:19.063 --> 38:21.364
                 You didn't walk
               down to the river

38:21.366 --> 38:23.500
                over a break up.

38:23.502 --> 38:26.002
           You walked down there
                         armed--

38:26.004 --> 38:28.538
            to the same location
        your uncle was arrested,

38:28.540 --> 38:30.507
        to prove you were tough.

38:30.509 --> 38:32.842
                  To get revenge
                 for your uncle.

38:32.844 --> 38:34.511
    - Objection, Your Honor!
          - Sustained.

38:34.513 --> 38:36.680
      - Dewan just wanted
        an explanation!

38:38.916 --> 38:41.017
    It was that cop's fault
        that he's dead!

38:41.019 --> 38:43.019
             - And you went down
    to the river to get revenge,

38:43.021 --> 38:44.621
                     didn't you?

38:44.623 --> 38:46.856
   You went down there, Michael,
                to kill a cop...

38:46.858 --> 38:48.024
    - Objection, Your Honor!
            - Right?

38:48.026 --> 38:50.593
    - Counsel is testifying!
           - Enough!

38:50.595 --> 38:53.596
         <i>[dramatic music]</i>

38:53.598 --> 39:01.738
               <i>â™ª </i>

39:10.948 --> 39:13.049
      - [exhales sharply]

39:23.494 --> 39:25.762
            - Peter.
          - Shambala.

39:25.764 --> 39:28.064
                 - Look at this.
        You got me eating carbs.

39:28.066 --> 39:30.467
- If it's any comfort,
I housed a whole pint

39:30.469 --> 39:32.869
of Haagen-Dazs last night.

39:32.871 --> 39:35.071
            - Aggravated battery
                 with a firearm.

39:35.073 --> 39:36.906
           Served as a juvenile.

39:38.743 --> 39:41.010
           - No way.
- I'm only gonna offer it once.

39:41.012 --> 39:43.580
- You ever had
an innocent client, Shambala?

39:46.917 --> 39:49.686
             - I've had hundreds
            who were not guilty.

40:00.731 --> 40:02.632
                           - No.

40:02.634 --> 40:04.501
- We should take it,
Peter.

40:04.503 --> 40:05.935
         - It's been three days.

40:05.937 --> 40:07.070
If the jury was going
to acquit,

40:07.072 --> 40:08.805
they'd be back already
and Green knows it.

40:08.807 --> 40:11.808
     - And you never seen a case
 go sideways at the last minute?

40:11.810 --> 40:13.943
- He could be out
in four years.

40:13.945 --> 40:15.578
    - And he would have admitted
                       his guilt

40:15.580 --> 40:17.747
          and this will be over.

40:17.749 --> 40:19.949
                         [sighs]

40:19.951 --> 40:21.751
              Do you really want
                to put this city

40:21.753 --> 40:23.853
              through this again
              if the jury hangs?

40:30.828 --> 40:32.929
- Only if Burgess and Roman
sign off on it.

40:43.774 --> 40:46.843
       - Absolutely not.
           - [sighs]

40:48.813 --> 40:50.613
            - What? Do you think
             you should do this?

40:52.116 --> 40:54.584
      - I see it's merits.

40:54.586 --> 40:56.586
           - [sighs]

40:56.588 --> 40:58.588
     Then he needs to admit
     he lied in open court.

40:58.590 --> 41:00.990
    - It's <i>nolo contendere.</i>

41:00.992 --> 41:04.194
 He won't dispute the charges.
           That's it.

41:04.196 --> 41:06.629
- Can we at least
get an apology?

41:06.631 --> 41:09.098
          To the CPD?
    - It's not gonna happen.

41:09.100 --> 41:11.100
- So the next guy
that shoots a cop

41:11.102 --> 41:12.702
thinks all he'll get
is four years?

41:12.704 --> 41:13.870
                         - Sean,
            he may be acquitted.

41:13.872 --> 41:15.672
                 That's the risk
              we're taking here.

41:15.674 --> 41:17.774
               Or, almost worse,
           the jury may be hung.

41:24.615 --> 41:26.483
              - It's up to Sean.

41:26.485 --> 41:28.685
                    He's the one
                   who got shot.

41:34.024 --> 41:37.527
      - We're all sleeping
    in our own beds tonight.

41:37.529 --> 41:39.629
    Let the city sleep too.

